Python Project - (Data from Prosper Loan)¶

by (Marcel Ezeokoye)¶

Introduction¶

This data set contains the customer's data from a loan company - Prosper. This dataset comprises of 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate , current loan status, borrower income, and many others.

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The Prosper dataset contains 113937 observations and 81 variables. Out of these 81 variables, the analysis would be focused on just 18 variables of interest to help with answering the research questions. A new dataset with the variables of interest was created with a structure of 94844 observations and 18 features. The loan dataset includes Eight categorical variables comprising of : ListingCreationDate, LoanStatus, ListingCategory, EmploymentStatus, IsBorrowerHomeowner,IncomeVerifiable,Occupation, BorrowerState and ten quantitative variables comprising of : Term, BorrowerAPR, BorrowerRate, LenderYield, EmploymentStatusDuration, StatedMonthlyIncome, LoanOriginalAmount, MonthlyLoanPayment, IncomeRange,DebtToIncomeRatio

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

The main features of interest from the prosper dataset are - factors that affect a loan's outcome status, factors that could enable a borrower have access to a loan, and ascertaining if EmploymentStatus and Income can facilitate loan request.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

The LoanStatus, BorrowerAPR, BorrowerRate, EmploymentStatus,IncomeRange are some of the features in the dataset that will enable me to carry out my analysis. Although, variables like DebtToIncomeRatio and MonthlyLoanPayment will help acertain to ability of borrowers to make installment payment ant intrests on their loans.

# Create a histogram to show the LoanOriginalAmount distribution
sns.histplot(loan.LoanOriginalAmount,color='green');

The distribution for the loan original amount is of a multimodal distribution with various peak variations at different price regions. However, there are outliers at the end of the distributin in the 28000 - 35000 range which depicts that a very low amount of persons where granted huge amount of loans as compared to the lower range of 15000 and below where more loan amount were granted.

Majority of the loans term have a 36 months lenght making 74.4% of the entire loan. while the remaining of the loan terms has a lenght of 60 and 12 months respectively compraising 24.1% and 1.5% of the loan term.

Conclusions¶

The loan dataset from Prosper loans had a large amount variables(81), but for the purpose of analysis eighteen(18) variables was selected. data wrangling and manupulation was done to prepare the data for analysis.

The main question that guided the exploration and analysis of the loan dataset are as follows: a. What factors enable one to obtain loan b. The reason people obtained laons from Prosper c. Is there a nexus between Loan status, Loan original amount and term.

a. From the charts, being employed and having a full time job is a major criteria for obtaining loans from prosper

b. Obviously,from the plot, the main reason people obtain loans is simply for debt consolidation i.e people borrowring loans to pay off several existing debts.

c.The loan status is affected by a variety of factors such as loan term which is the length of the loan. The loan term is however dependent on the loan original amount as smsller loan amount get smaller loan term while bigger loan amount get higher term.

Finally, we observed that the higher the loan original amount, the higher the monthly loan payments cutting across the various loan status types.
